  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2006-12-05",
    "date": "2008-08-21T12:09:09Z",
    "text": "Tax Code Termination Act - Mandates the termination of the Internal Revenue Code after December 31, 2010, except for self-employment taxes, Federal Insurance Contributions Act taxes, and Railroad Retirement taxes.\n\nDeclares that any new federal tax system should be a simple and fair system that: (1) provides tax relief for working Americans; (2) protects the rights of taxpayers and reduces tax collection abuses; (3) eliminates the bias against savings and investment; (4) promotes economic growth and job creation; and (5) does not penalize marriage or families.\n\nRequires that the new federal tax system be approved by Congress in its final form by July 4, 2010."
  },
